<HL>
   Business Brief -- Pansophic Systems Inc.:
   Two Investors Announce
   They Have a 5.7% Stake
</HL>
<DATE>
12/27/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A10
</SO>
<CO>
   PNS
</CO>
<IN>
SOFTWARE (SOF)
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   George Soros and Purnendu Chatterjee said they hold a 5.7%
stake in Pansophic Systems Inc.'s common shares outstanding.
   In a filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission,
the investors said they hold 1,026,800 Pansophic shares,
including 806,800 shares bought from Oct. 29 to Dec. 20 at $7
to $8.25 each.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   According to the filing, the shares were bought for
investment reasons.
   In Lisle, Ill., a Pansophic official said the software
concern had no immediate comment.
</TEXT>
